        <h2 class="asset-name entry-title"><a href="http://pandasthumb.org/archives/2014/02/sarcodes-sangui.html" rel="bookmark">Sarcodes sanguinea</a></h2>
        <div class="asset-meta">
            <span class="byline">
    
                By 
                <span class="vcard author"><a class="fn url" href="http://www.mines.edu/~mmyoung">Matt Young</a></span> on <abbr class="published" title="2014-02-24T12:00:00-06:00">February 24, 2014 12:00 PM</abbr>
    
            </span>

            <span class="separator">|</span> <a href="http://pandasthumb.org/archives/2014/02/sarcodes-sangui.html#comments">2 Comments</a> <a href="http://pandasthumb.org/archives/2014/02/sarcodes-sangui.html#comment-last">(new)</a>
            

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="asset-content entry-content">

        <div class="asset-body">
            <div class="kw-format"><p>Photograph by <strong>Jim Norton</strong>.</p>

<p>Photography contest, Honorable Mention.</p>

<div class="kw-figure" style=" width:577px;"><div class="kw-figure-img"><img src="http://pandasthumb.org/archives/2014/02/22/Norton.snow-planr.JPG" alt="Norton.snow-planr.JPG" width="571" height="1399" /></div>
<p><big><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarcodes" rel="external "><em>Sarcodes sanguinea</em></a> – snow plant, a saprophytic plant with no chlorophyll.  King’s Canyon National Park, California, July 3, 2010.</big>
</p>

