<P class=MsoNormal><SPAN style="mso-ansi-language: EN-AU">Williams, G. C. 
(1975). <I>Sex and evolution</I>.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; 
</SPAN>Princeton University Press: Princeton, New Jersey.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -72.0pt"><SPAN 
style="mso-ansi-language: EN-AU">Wimsatt, W. C. (1981). Units of selection and 
the structure of the multi-level genome. In:<I>PSA <SPAN 
style="mso-tab-count: 1">&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>1980 - Proceedings of the 1980 
Biennial Meeting of the PSA, Volume 2 </I>(Asquith, P. D., and Giere, R. N., 
eds.). PSA: Michigan. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -72.0pt"><SPAN 
style="mso-ansi-language: EN-AU">Wimsatt, W. C. (1986). Developmental 
constraints, generative entrenchment, and the innate-acquired distinction. In: 
<I>Integrating Scientific Disciplines</I> (Bechtel, W., ed.) Dordrecht: Martinus 
Nijhoff.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: -72.0pt"><SPAN 
style="mso-ansi-language: EN-AU">Wright, S. (1977). <I>Evolution and the 
genetics of populations. Vol. 4: Variability within and between natural 
populations.</I> University of Chicago Press: Chicago.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 
style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt; TEXT-INDENT: -36pt; tab-stops: -72.0pt"><SPAN 
style="mso-ansi-language: EN-AU">Wright, S. (1935). Evolution of populations in 
approximate equilibrium. <I>J. Genet</I>. <B>30</B>, 
257-266.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P></DIV><SPAN 
style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-AU; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><BR 
style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always; mso-break-type: section-break" 
clear=all></SPAN>
<DIV class=Section3>
<P class=MsoNormal style="tab-stops: center 225.65pt"><B><SPAN 
style="mso-ansi-language: EN-AU"><![if !supportEmptyParas]><![endif]>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P></DIV></BODY></HTML>
