    <tr>
        <td width="516" height="126" colspan="11" namo_textbox="4,4,4,4,3,3,3,3,1,0">
            <p align="center" style="line-height:120%; margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0;"><font face="Arial"><span style="font-size:12pt;"><b>Observations 
            support Big Bang cosmology</b></span></font></p>
            <p style="line-height:120%; margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0;" align="center">&nbsp;</p>
            <p style="line-height:120%; margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0;" align="left"><font face="Arial"><span style="font-size:10pt;">Third 
            Year data from the Wilkinson Microwave Anisotropy Probe have been 
            published. These data support the Standard Model of Cosmology extremely 
            well, with detailed support for a Cold Dark Matter model with flat 
            or nearly flat universe, and a cosmological&nbsp;constant-like Dark 
            Energy. Inflation is strongly supported. The signature of gravity 
            waves was not detected but not ruled out. </span></font><a href="third_year_wmap.htm"><span style="font-size:10pt;"><b><font face="Arial" color="#CC0000">Go 
            here</font></b></span></a></p>
